Thanks to a new course this year at Harvard University, all university students sleep more in an attempt to fight the growing machist culture of studying all night drinking caffeine.
One teacher found that students at university number one in the world do not usually have any idea about the basic care of oneself.
Charles Czeisler, professor of sleep medicine at Harvard School of Medicine, and a specialist at Brigham and Women's Hospital designed the course, it is believed that the first of his class in the U.S.
