Syria is ready for the return of refugees, says the Minister for Foreign Affairs
Syria states that it is ready for the voluntary return of refugees and calls for help in rebuilding a war-torn country that has been going on for more than seven years.
In an earlier speech by the United Nations General Assembly, Foreign Minister Walid al-Maualem said that the conditions of the country were improving.
“The situation on the ground is now more stable and secure thanks to the progress that has been made in the fight against terrorism,” he said.
The government continues to rehabilitate areas destroyed by terrorists in an attempt to restore normalcy.
All the conditions for the voluntary return to the country of refugees who had to abandon it due to terrorism and unilateral economic measures that affected their daily lives and livelihoods are already given.
The UN estimates that, since the war began in 2011, more than 5.5 million Syrians have fled the country.
There are another six million people still living in the country who need humanitarian assistance.
Al-Maualem acknowledged that the Syrian regime would be grateful for the help of rebuilding the devastated country.
But he also stressed that he would not accept conditional aid or aid from the countries that promoted insurgency.
